<div class="quotetitle">Ivo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />3. Don't use PNG, you need to use bitmaps. The SKIN text refers to the numeric ID of the bitmap resource.<br /></div><br /><br /><br />Got this working now, thanks.<br /><br />On a related note (useful info if someone is searching) to have 32-bit bitmaps actually use an alpha channel, you have to manually create it from a selection.<br /><br />This can be done by selecting the areas you want to be opaque (Magic Wand or CTRL+click layers) then use the &quot;Save selection as channel&quot; button on the Channels palette.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4261">davestewart</a> — Fri Oct 02, 2015 3:37 am</p><hr />
