1. No, the start menu closes when you click somewhere else.<br />2. You can edit the skin while it is in use. Then just press the Win key to see it. If the timestamp is changed, the menu will reload it.<br />3. Don't use PNG, you need to use bitmaps. The SKIN text refers to the numeric ID of the bitmap resource.<br /><br />1. I don't know.<br />2. You need to open the file as a resource. File -&gt; Open, then select the file, then use the dropdown next to the Open button to select to open as a resource.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Thu Oct 01, 2015 8:20 am</p><hr />
