<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5216&amp;p=22656#p22656"><![CDATA[
The settings in the XML are mostly independent of the skin. Most of the settings control the behavior of the menu. Some of the settings are related to the skin (show frames, use large font, etc). Basically the skin determines what settings exist and the XML determines what the current choices for them are. If you want a very specific skin you don't even need to have any skin settings.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Wed Sep 30, 2015 2:40 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
